{"body": "@josevalim I'm seeing 1.9.3p0 code now. According to uri/common.rb,\r\nURI.parse calls DEFAULT_PARSER.parse only, and Parser.new is assigned to DEFAULT_PARSER.\r\n\r\nAnd it seems that URI::Parser#parse will never change internal state.\r\n\r\n...\r\n\r\nBut, I think that there were `URI.parser` (AS's core_ext) method for 1.8.x and 1.9.x compatibility now.\r\nThus, should we deprecate `URI.parser` method and use `URI.parse` ?\r\n(or, on the contrary, could you merge this PR ?)\r\n\r\n```\r\n# URI.parser.parse(uri_string)\r\nURI.parse(uri_string)\r\n```\r\n", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/3549270", "created_at": "2012-01-18T17:07:00Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/4521#issuecomment-3549270", "updated_at": "2012-01-18T17:30:17Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 4521, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/kennyj", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/1f0b221851379759360d7130dabdfa53?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F54ecc28e9508fcf28363014b0d1b4eb8.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/received_events", "gravatar_id": "1f0b221851379759360d7130dabdfa53", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "kennyj", "type": "User", "id": 13426, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/kennyj/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523824e1bd3543c15100ec82"}, "id": 3549270, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/4521"}
